x4freetext: Data tables.
50 mu-m thick-purity natural Cu foils(99.9) were
included in five composite foil stacks irradiated at
various times with the external proton beam of the
separated-sector cyclotron facility.

The results were compared with theoretical
predictions obtained by means of the computer code
ALICE within the framework of the geometry-dependent
hybrid model of preequilibrium emission, combined with
Weisskopf-Ewing evaporation theory.
